<DOC><DOCNO> AP880827-0045 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-27-88 0521EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-BoatCrash 1stLd-Writethru a0461 08-27 0161</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Boat Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0461,0161</SECOND><HEAD>Peruvian Sub Collides With Japanese Fishing Boat, Three Killed</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: New throughout to UPDATE with submarine sinking, otherdetails.</NOTE><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Peruvian submarine collided with a Japanesefishing boat and sank off Peru, leaving at least three people deadand 28 missing, the Japanese Foreign Ministry said today.   The ministry said all the casualties were among the 53 crewmembers of the submarine. Twenty-two of the submarine's crewmembers were rescued, the ministry said.   The ministry, quoting preliminary reports from the JapaneseEmbassy in Lima, said the submarine collided with the No. 8Kyowa-maru, a 412-ton tuna fishing boat, Friday evening. It saidthere were 20 people on board the tuna boat.   Ministry officials said the collision took place off Callao, aport north of the capital city, Lima.   The fishing boat suffered some cracks on the bow, ministryofficials said.   Cause of the accident and other details were not immediatelyavailable.</TEXT></DOC>